  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 7079.71 sitting below the 7098 flip strike in a PIN regime, dealers are currently net buying the dip to hedge their long gamma positions, providing stabilizing support. The massive positive gamma wall at 7200 (+7023M) will create significant selling pressure on any rally attempt, while the thick cluster of gamma walls between 7100-7150 should act as intermediate resistance levels that cap upside momentum. Watch 7065 as the max negative gamma strike where dealer buying accelerates if breached, and monitor the 7098 flip level as a key regime boundary.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect mean-reverting price action with upside capped near 7100-7150 range.",
